2017 WW01 Bakerville/SKX-D Gold Release Announcement (BKC #7)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW01 Bakerville/SKX-D Gold release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n Linux/\n \n VMWare/\n \n Windows\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

o   Test coverage:  

\xc2\xa7     SKX-D L0 VIS SoC: Run P1 and P2 test cases on RHEL 7.2, Windows2016 and VMWare6.0.

HW\nrework:

    \n
  • No HW rework\n need for Yuba City fab3 board.
    • \n
  • jumper\n setting refers to this link.
    • \n

 

Work around:

    \n
  • Secure Boot\n only can run in UEFI mode, so if we want secure boot can work and let bios\n load UEFI Oprom, we need Disable\n this option. 
    • \n

EDKII Menu -> Boot\nOptions -> EFI INT10 workaround

    \n
  • When you flash onboard Aspeed BMC, in order to\n detect onboard dTPM in AC cycle, you need run below IPMI command in UEFI\n Shell:
    • \n

#cmdtool  20 C0 3f 07

BKC Artifactory Access

Link (SH server): https://ubit-artifactory-sh.intel.com

Link (OR server): https://ubit-artifactory-or.intel.com

Steps for applying the permission:

  • Go to EAM website: https://eam.intel.com/EAMWeb/RequestAccess/DisplayTree.aspx?TopNode=757719
  • Apply for the "Project viewer" role
  • Use your windows credentials for authentication

BKC One Stop Shop

Link: https://dcg-oss.intel.com

Steps for applying the permission:

  • Go to EAM website: https://eam.intel.com/EAMWeb/RequestAccess/DisplayTree.aspx?TopNode=829001
  • Navigate to:"BKC -- Purley"
  • Apply for the "User" or "Ingredient Owner" role
  • Use your windows credentials for authentication
